  "text": "We used the LightGen plug-in of HDRShop [HDRShop] to decompose the environment maps into 300 light sources. We first test our approach using the parametric sky model of [CITATION_1] to generate two different times of the day. We used linear blending and our method on the two environment maps to render images at intermediate times of the day (Fig. 15) . Linear blending does not capture the motion of the sun and renders fixed shadows with only changing intensities. In the displacement interpolation result, shadows rotate similarly to the reference image obtained with the parametric model.",
